For a reversible elementary reaction of the form $\sum_i 
u_i' M_i ightleftharpoons \sum_i 
u_i'' M_i$, the net reaction rate (rate of progress) $q$ is determined by the difference between the forward and reverse rates, proportional to the product of reactant and product concentrations respectively:
$$ q = k_f(T) \prod_i c_i^{
u_i'} - k_r(T) \prod_i c_i^{
u_i''} $$
